<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-747-726  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 747 726.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  August 14 1990 v4 n28 p20(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Images, documents Topic of retrieval. (Verity Inc. introducesTopic Document Retrieval System) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Said, Carolyn.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Verity Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Topic (Search software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSoftware PackagesDocument Management SystemsInformation Storage and Retrieval.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Distributed DBMS runs on Macs, hostsandM;By Carolyn SaidandM;Mountain View, Calif.andP;  -- Corporations with mountains of information tostore, digest and sort can add Verity Inc.'s Topic Document Retrieval Systemfor the Macintosh to their arsenal of data-handling tools.andM;Based on a distributed-processing model, Topic runs over Apple-Share, NJS and3Com networks.andP;  Individual workstations, including Macintoshes, IBM PCs, Sunsand DEC VAXes, act as networked Topic Retrieval Clients, which field userrequests, search the distributed database and quickly present results inrelevance-ranked order.andM;Mac clients use a graphical interface and object-oriented query language toperform searches.andP;  Similar graphical interfaces for IBM PCs and X Windowplatforms will be released this year.andM;Verity assists new sites in creating the core of the search architecture, aknowledge base of &quot;topics.&quot; Topic also uses a Database Builder, a suite ofapplication utilities, to create, modify and maintain Topic databases.andM;Topic offers HyperLink connections to images, annotations and documents; anapplication programming interface; and an optional SQL-Bridge interface tostructured query language relational databases, such as Oracle and Sybase.andM;Verity also offers Topic Real-Time, which connects to live data feeds fromsources such as news wires and electronic mail.andP;  Topic Real-Time dynamicallyindexes and profiles incoming information and alerts the user when relevantnews arrives.andP;  Verity also will be developing Topic Real-Time services forDow Jones andamp; Co.'s new DowVision on-line news and information service (seeMacWEEK, June 5).andM;Topic prices range from $695 for a Retrieval Client to $15,000 to $150,000for network configurations.andP;  Pricing includes support and training fromVerity.andP;  Mac clients will be available by the end of this year, Verity said.andM;Verity Inc. is located at 1550 Plymouth, Mountain View, Calif.andP;  94043-1230;(415) 960-7600.andO;</TEXT></DOC>